org.agilewiki.jactor2.core.messages.impl

Class OneWayResponseProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.agilewiki.jactor2.core.messages.impl.OneWayResponseProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AsyncResponseProcessor<java.lang.Void>

    public final class OneWayResponseProcessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements AsyncResponseProcessor<java.lang.Void>
    Used to flag a request as a 1-way message. The singleton serves as a flag, so no response is ever returned and consequently the processAsyncResponse method should never actually be invoked. This is the AsyncResponseProcessor used when null is passed as the second argument in the send method.

        The processAsyncResponse method accepts the response of a request.

        This method need not be thread-safe, as it is always invoked from the same light-weight thread (targetReactor) that passed the AsyncRequest and AsyncResponseProcessor objects.
